<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-14T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-14T03:00:00-05:00" n="701" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d701">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13277: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Josselyn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-14T16:00:00+08:00">November 14, 1935—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 14—3:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>58. Peiping’s November 13, 2 p.m.,<note n="18" xml:id="d701fn18">Not
                                found in Department files.</note> and my November 13, 4 p.m. Yachow
                            missionaries have arrived in Kiating. I telegraphed yesterday to
                            Tatsienlu but have not yet received a reply; the Hankow telegraph office
                            reported the wire open. Repeated to Peiping, Nanking.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Josselyn</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>